# StockEase Cursor Rules — V7 · May 2026

## NEVER break these rules

### Error & Empty States
- NEVER show raw DioException, stack traces, or HTTP codes to users
- ALWAYS use FriendlyLoadError / HexaErrorCard for error states
- Empty page = icon + message + action button. NEVER a blank white page.
- Section header (TODAY / EARLIER) with nothing below it = REMOVE the header entirely.

### Search — CRITICAL RULE
- NEVER call ref.read(stockListQueryProvider.notifier).state = ... on search text change
- ALWAYS filter locally using a computed getter on the already-loaded list.
- Search TextField onChanged: setState(() => _searchQuery = v.toLowerCase().trim()) — ONLY THIS. No provider writes.
- Only call API on: pull-to-refresh, first load, period change, explicit retry.

### Float Precision — CRITICAL
- Integer check: ALWAYS `(n - n.roundToDouble()).abs() < 0.001`. NEVER `n == n.roundToDouble()`.
- Prefer `n.round().toString()` over `n.toStringAsFixed(0)` for integer display.

### State Management
- NEVER call setState() inside ref.listen() directly.
- ALWAYS use WidgetsBinding.instance.addPostFrameCallback(() => setState((){})) inside ref.listen.
- After stock patch/update: ALWAYS invalidate stockListProvider AND stockAuditPeriodProvider.
- ALWAYS guard providers: if (session == null) return AsyncValue.data(const []);
- Period state is GLOBAL: appSelectedPeriodProvider — home + reports read same.

### Layout — Mobile First (360px min width)
- Max 3 columns in any list row. NEVER 4 columns.
- TabBar with ≥ 3 tabs: ALWAYS isScrollable: true, tabAlignment: TabAlignment.start
- Filter chips for 5+ options: ALWAYS use bottom sheet, never inline rows.
- NEVER horizontal SingleChildScrollView for filter chips — use Wrap + bottom sheet.
- NEVER overflow on 360px. Use Expanded/Flexible inside Row.

### Navigation
- ALL sub-page AppBar back buttons MUST use context.pop() not Navigator.pop()
- NEVER Navigator.of(context).pop() in shell routes

### Typography (enforce everywhere)
- AppBar title: fontSize 18, w600
- Section/card title: fontSize 16, w600
- Item name (list row): fontSize 14, w700
- Subtitle (code, category, qty): fontSize 11, normal, grey.shade600
- Stats number (home dashboard): fontSize 24, w900, colored
- Stats label: fontSize 10, w500, grey.shade600
- Badge/chip text: fontSize 10, w500

### Role-Based Display
- OWNER only: ₹ prices, rates, profit, UPI/payment, all financial totals
- OWNER + MANAGER: purchase history, reports, contacts, supplier rates
- ALL roles: stock quantities (no prices), item names, categories
- NEVER compute financial totals in Flutter — backend only.
- Settings: entire maintenance payment section hidden from non-owner

### Performance
- Keep-alive ping /health every 10 min after session bootstrap
- Tab switch: only invalidate providers if last fetch > 5 min ago

## Fix Order (strict)
HIDDEN-CRITICAL → SEARCH-FIX → UX-STOCK → UX-HOME → UX-REPORTS →
UX-STAFF → UX-CATALOG → UX-PURCHASE → UX-BARCODE → NEW-PAGES → FEATURES
